For this lab just have only one worker node, make sure your master node already have Taint at installation time. 
(if you start cluster installation with one master and one or more worker nodes, so installer apply the taint by default on master node to prevent any application pods to get scheduled on master node)

Taint Lab:

What is Taint?

  Node taint is used where you don't want to schedule a application pods on a specific nodes.
  It has three Type of Taint Effects:

    NoSchedule:  (This is the mostly used taint Effect)

       Pods that do not tolerate the taint will not be scheduled on the node.
    
    NoExecute:

      Pods that do not tolerate the taint will be evicted from the node if already running, and not scheduled there in the future.

    PreferNoSchedule:

    Kubernetes tries to avoid placing pods that donâ€™t tolerate the taint on the node, but may still schedule them if no other options are available.


Use two or atleast one worker node


